ABUJA â€“ Senator Ali-Modu Sheriff, a leading aspirant for Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has declared his readiness to abide by any position President Muhammadu Buhari may take on who emerges as the new chairman of the party. Although no official position has been said about the choice of President Mohammadu Buhari on the Consensus Chairman of the party, reports have linked the option to former Nasarawa State governor, Senator Abdullahi Adamu. Senator Sheriff said he decided to offer himself to serve as Chairman of APC because of his capacity and strength of character for leadership, believing that if given the opportunity, he will lead the party to victory in 2023. Addressing journalists in his office on this and sundry issues surrounding the new party Chairman, the former Borno State governor said whilst the position of the president has not been communicated to him or any aspirant for that matter, that he will support whoever the president chooses to lead the party.